<h2>SECURITY  OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION</h2>
<p>MYTCG  is committed to protecting the security of your Personal Information. We use a  variety of security technologies and procedures to help protect your personal  information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. For example, we store  the Personal Information you provide on computer servers with limited access  that are located in controlled facilities. Additionally, when we transmit  sensitive Personal Information (such as a credit card number) over the  Internet, we protect it through the use of encryption, such as the Secure  Socket Layer (SSL) protocol and the like.</p>
<p>MYTCG uses commercially reasonable  physical, managerial, and technical safeguards. We cannot, however, ensure or  warrant the security of any information that MYTCG receives on your behalf to operate  the MYTCG Services or that you transmit to MYTCG and you do so at your own  risk. We also cannot guarantee that such information may not be accessed,  disclosed, altered, or destroyed by breach of any of our physical, technical,  or managerial safeguards.</p>
<p>If MYTCG learns of a security  systems breach, then we may attempt to notify you electronically so that you  can take appropriate protective steps. MYTCG may post a notice on the MYTCG  Services if a security breach occurs. Depending on where you live, you may have  a legal right to receive notice of a security breach in writing.</p>
<h2>PROTECTION  OF CHILDREN'S PERSONAL INFORMATION</h2>
